{"type":null,"faqId":26411,"title":"Invisible User Experience — Accelerating Your Phone","answer":"<p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;line-height:12.0pt;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:center;\" align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'minorBidi','serif';\">Invisible User\nExperience </span></b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif'\">—\n</span><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\">Accelerating\nYour Phone</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-indent:21.0pt;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';margin-left:36.75pt;text-indent:-36.75pt;\n\"><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Microsoft YaHei','sans-serif';\n\"><span>I.<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\">Why does my phone get slow?</span></b><span style=\"font-family:'Microsoft YaHei','sans-serif';\n\"> </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-indent:21.0pt;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in;\n\"><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Microsoft YaHei','sans-serif';\n\"><span>1.<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\">Hardware Configuration</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-indent:15.75pt;\n\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'minorBidi','serif';\">Your phone performance is determined\nby the CPU, GPU, and internal storage space. The applications are providing\nmore and more functions. Realizing the functions and effects of the\napplications consumes many system resources, such as the CPU and internal\nstorage. The phone performance may also be degraded by hardware aging.\nReasonably use your phone to prolong its lifespan. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\n\">2. Applications</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-indent:15.75pt;\n\"><span style=\"font-family:\n'minorBidi','serif';\">Some applications automatically start\nduring phone startup and may run in the background, taking up your phone's CPU\nand internal storage and increasing battery power consumption. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;text-indent:21.0pt;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';margin-left:36.75pt;text-indent:-36.75pt;\n\"><b><span style=\"\nfont-family:'Microsoft YaHei','sans-serif';\n\"><span>II.<span style=\"font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\">Accelerating your phone</span></b><b><span style=\"font-family:'Microsoft YaHei','sans-serif';\n\"> </span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\n\">1. Prevent applications from automatically starting\nduring startup.</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\">The most effective\nway of saving up your phone's CPU and internal storage is to forbid\napplications from starting during startup. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\n\">2. Monitor and clear exceptions in time, and download\napplications from trusted sources only. </span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\">If your phone\nfails to run smoothly for a long time, there may be process exceptions that\ntake up the CPU or IO resources. In this case, find out and end the exceptional\nprocesses. To view your phone's CPU usage, go to <b>Settings</b> &gt; <b>Developer\noptions</b>, and select <b>Show CPU usage</b>.\n</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';margin-left:15.75pt;text-indent:-15.75pt;\"><span style=\"\nfont-family:'minorBidi','serif';\">To monitor and end\nexceptional processes: </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\">Go to <b>Settings</b> &gt; <b>Manage apps</b> &gt; <b>All</b>,\ntouch the application in question, and touch <b>Force stop</b>. In this way, this application will not automatically\nstart. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\"><span style=\"font-family:'minorBidi','serif';\">Note: Download\napplications from trusted sources only, such as Huawei App Center. </span></p>\n<br>\n</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"790","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1433163548000,"seriesProductName":"","visitedTimes":4,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"Invisible User Experience — Accelerating Your Phone","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}